	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Nov 26th 9:52 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've been camping Grimrot for an entire weekend straight worth of PH's, camping out between PH. I cant get him to spawn, i finally did but then attempting to login my CLR, EQ crashed and i lost it to rotting. I had killed the PH at 10 am, and grimrot spawned somewhere around 3am. So lets try and clear stuff up in some replies to this post.<br><br>FACT OR MYTH:<br><br>1.) Killing the PH at "X" time results in "Y" version of Grimrot Spawning. (if fact, what time results what grimrot)<br><br>2.) Killing the skeletons in the surrounding area, excluding the putrid skeleton PH, hurts  or helps the spawning of Grimrot (if fact, which one)<br><br>--Now i'll go and answer some that I know the answer to--<br><br>3.) You cannot check your faction status with  Camlend Serbold to see if you're faction is high enough<br><br>Myth - tell Camlend "I came to defend life" and if he says sorry that he only entrusts the quest to his most loyal members, then you need to up it, if he goes on and tells you about Lord Grimrot, you're in the clear!<br><br>4.) Dark Elves are screwed and cannot get this Aegis of Life<br><br>Myth - I have dark elven cleric, and they can only worth innoruuk, but your starting faction is Dubious to most of qeynos (except the caster guild, watch out!) Just hand 2GP at a time to Lashun Novashine until you can run the sash quest which i believe gives more faction "points" beware it takes about 600gp to get to Apprehensive from Dubious. But boy is it worth it!<br><br>5.) 2 People can multi-quest this if each has 1 of the parts.<br><br>Fact - as long as the designated PAL/CLR for the Aegis has at least 1 of the items. The other person can hand in theirs first, then you hand in yours last to get your Aegis. Beware, BOTH people must have the needed faction or you'll loose your items!<br><br>-- Feel free to add to this list so we can hopefully clear up the mystery of this quest and get all the facts down straight! --<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
